lead_paragraph: Consumer spending in the United States rose 1 percent in April, the largest amount in more than six years, led by a big jump in purchases of autos and other durable goods.

headline.print_headline: Market Is Mixed Despite Utility Gains
headline.main: Wall St. Is Mixed as Investors Weigh Economic Data

snippet: Consumer spending in the United States rose 1 percent in April, the largest amount in more than six years, led by a big jump in purchases of autos and other durable goods.
abstract: Stocks struggle to mixed close, with energy stocks dipping due to decline in price of oil, discounting gains made by utilities and phone companies.
